The paper focuses on using Wasserstein GANs for single image super-resolution, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the performance of different training objectives and architectures, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of GANs for image processing also relates to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
